Z(\frac{\partial Z}{\partial x}-\frac{\partial Z}{\partial y})=(x+y)^2+Z^2
Z = \pm \sqrt{e^{2c_1(x+y)+2x}-(x+y)^2}
A
f(t)=\exp(A(t/2))
 u=\frac{x-y}{2},\ v=\frac{x+y}{2},\ F(u,v)=Z(u+v,v-u). 
 \frac12\frac{\partial }{\partial u}F^2(u,v)=4v^2+F^2(u,v). 
 \frac12\ln(4v^2+F^2(u,v))=u+\frac12 A(v), 
 F(u,v)=\pm \sqrt{e^{2u}e^{A(v)}-4v^2}. 
 Z(x,y)=F(\frac{x-y}{2},\frac{x+y}{2})=\pm\sqrt{f(x+y)e^{x-y}-(x+y)^2}, 
